         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>
      </accessrestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_9403f0f45e86a8001ad8b9bb2f7167e7">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Agur Gilbert Family Papers (MS 998). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>
      </prefercite>
      <bioghist id="aspace_6d5ccbbd169509136682390f21f5b52e">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Agur Gilbert was born on May 2, 1807, in Huntington, Connecticut. He died on January 23, 1887, in Derby, Connecticut. His wife, Mary Louise Johnson, was born on September 28, 1808, and died on January 24, 1864, in Derby, Connecticut. They were married on February 4, 1830, in Derby, and had five children.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_83ae8562affbc5c39e9e3115113afd12">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Papers of the family of Agur Gilbert, wood turners and toy makers of Derby, Connecticut. Consists of family correspondence, business letters, and account books, primarily for A. Gilbert and Son.</p>
      </scopecontent>
